      <hedline>
        <hl1>Laptops Stolen at School</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Nineteen laptop computers with estimated value of $40,000 are stolen from elementary school in Queens (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Nineteen laptop computers with an estimated value of $40,000 were stolen from an elementary school in Queens, the police said yesterday.</p>
        <p>School officials reported the theft on Friday morning, after the computers were found to be missing from Public School 68 at 59-09 St. Felix Avenue in the Glendale section, the police said.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Nineteen laptop computers with an estimated value of $40,000 were stolen from an elementary school in Queens, the police said yesterday.</p>
        <p>School officials reported the theft on Friday morning, after the computers were found to be missing from Public School 68 at 59-09 St. Felix Avenue in the Glendale section, the police said.</p>
        <p>Detectives from the 104th Precinct are investigating the theft, the police said.</p>
      </block>
